                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d29">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10137: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-19T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 19, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>685. During my conversation with the Minister for Foreign Affairs yesterday he
                    asked me to say to you that he hoped that the United States would be represented
                    at least as an observer when the League takes up China’s appeal in regard to
                    Sino-Japanese hostilities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
